description:
On April 12th, Guatemala prohibits until April 20th, 4 am,
"a) the locomotion, circulation and transit to any place in the Republic, by land, air or sea, for any trip of a recreational, social or family nature;
b) visits to beaches, lakes, lagoons, rivers or similar;
c) attendance at any activity in public areas, tourist or historical places. Military flights, ambulances, fumigation or duly authorized emergency transfers are excepted."
 UPDATE: The prohibition of any trip of a personal, recreational, social or family nature was set to last until April 12th, this was extended to April 20th, 4am
